NOTES
	For PuTTY uses you should set the connection to use UTF-8 otherwise you get some really weird behaviors.
	For PuTTY you'll also need to install a font that has Powerline support. Those can be found on the Powerline-Font repository on github.

DEPENDENCIES
	Native
	* exuberant-ctags
	* fontconfig

	Python
	* mercurial
	* psutil
	* powerline

	Perl
	* perltidy
	* podtidy
	* perlcritic

PowerLine Instructions
(User)
	wget https://github.com/Lokaltog/powerline/raw/develop/font/PowerlineSymbols.otf https://github.com/Lokaltog/powerline/raw/develop/font/10-powerline-symbols.conf
	mkdir -p ~/.fonts/
	mv PowerlineSymbols.otf ~/.fonts/
	fc-cache -vf ~/.fonts
	mkdir -p ~/.config/fontconfig/conf.d/
	mv 10-powerline-symbols.conf ~/.config/fontconfig/conf.d/

(Global)
	wget https://github.com/Lokaltog/powerline/raw/develop/font/PowerlineSymbols.otf https://github.com/Lokaltog/powerline/raw/develop/font/10-powerline-symbols.conf
	sudo mv PowerlineSymbols.otf /usr/share/fonts/
	sudo fc-cache -vf
	sudo mv 10-powerline-symbols.conf /etc/fonts/conf.d

